://buddypress.org/developers/wrkngwrkng/a, a href=http://buddypress.org/developers/xmailrxmailr/a, a href=http://buddypress.org/developers/xmailrxmailr/a, a href=http://buddypress.org/developers/yoavfyoavf/a, a href=http://buddypress.org/developers/zahirtaszahirtas/a, a href=http://buddypress.org/developers/zanzoonzanzoon/a, a href=http://buddypress.org/developers/zheng1212zheng1212/a/p";s:7:"pubdate";s:31:"Thu, 30 Apr 2009 20:24:31 +0000";s:2:"dc";a:1:{s:7:"creator";s:9:"apeatling";}s:7:"summary";s:12704:"pI#8217;m happy to announce that version 1.0 of a href=http://buddypress.org/aboutBuddyPress/a is now a href=http://buddypress.org/download/available for download/a./p\npThis release marks over a year of solid development, starting from the roots of the a href=http://chickspeak.com/ChickSpeak/a project, all the way to the blossoming developer community I see interacting on this site everyday./p\npThis is just the first step on a long road ahead. So much is possible now that we have a solid WordPress-based social framework to build upon./p\npThe status updates and gallery components are next on the roadmap, you can expect to see versions of those components appearing later this year. We#8217;ll also be going through the hundreds of enhancement tickets we#8217;ve received, and with your help prioritizing them for future versions./p\npI#8217;m most excited to see what plugin developers and theme designers can come up with. Even in the pre-release stages, a href=http://buddypress.org/extend/plugins/plugins/a to extend and add functionality have already been popping up. If you#8217;re a plugin developer or theme designer, be sure to check out the a href=http://codex.buddypress.org/how-to-guides/creating-a-custom-buddypress-component/skeleton component/a and a href=http://codex.buddypress.org/how-to-guides/creating-a-custom-buddypress-theme/skeleton theme/a. These packages will provide you with a solid starting point to build BuddyPress components and custom themes from./p\npI#8217;d also like to give some serious thanks to the community that has rallied around this project. I was told that getting people excited and involved with a new OSS project can be one of the hardest tasks to accomplish. I#8217;m really bowled over that so many people have become involved with BuddyPress development and feedback on a daily basis./p\npI#8217;d like to give a mention to every developer who has helped with the project, whether it be with tickets, advice, feedback or support:/p\npa href=http://buddypress.org/developers/adrenalisadrenalis/a, a href=http://buddypress.org/developers/ageeshkgageeshkg/a, a href=http://buddypress.org/developers/andyandy/a, a href=http://buddypress.org/developers/andrea_randrea_r/a, a href=http://buddypress.org/developers/arghagainarghagain/a, a href=http://buddypress.org/developers/arturo84arturo84/a, a href=http://buddypress.org/developers/armchairGeneralarmchairGeneral/a, a href=http://buddypress.org/developers/atraxatrax/a, a href=http://buddypress.org/developers/barrybarry/a, a href=http://buddypress.org/developers/beaulebensbeaulebens/a, a href=http://buddypress.org/developers/bebopcoolbebopcool/a, a href=http://buddypress.org/developers/belogicalbelogical/a, a href=http://buddypress.org/developers/benny148148benny148148/a, a href=http://buddypress.org/developers/berconbercon/a, a href=http://buddypress.org/developers/bergstenbergsten/a, a href=http://buddypress.org/developers/bflorabflora/a, a href=http://buddypress.org/developers/blogestudioblogestudio/a, a href=http://buddypress.org/developers/bloombloom/a, a href=http://buddypress.org/developers/bluestrawbluestraw/a, a href=http://buddypress.org/developers/borkwebborkweb/a, a href=http://buddypress.org/developers/bpress-trbpress-tr/a, a href=http://buddypress.org/developers/brianbreybrianbrey/a, a href=http://buddypress.org/developers/burtadsitburtadsit/a, a href=http://buddypress.org/developers/buzz_lightyearbuzz_lightyear/a, a href=http://buddypress.org/de