img title=themptationPress src=http://weblogtoolscollection.com/b2-img/2009/04/themptationpress.jpg alt=themptationPress width=200 height=46 //a/p\npTwo column theme, with four widget areas, dropdown menu, six background variations and ad management system/p\npAre you a theme author? a href=http://weblogtoolscollection.com/submit-news/Submit your theme/a to us./p";s:7:"pubdate";s:31:"Sat, 25 Apr 2009 21:12:17 +0000";s:2:"dc";a:1:{s:7:"creator";s:7:"Perurry";}s:7:"summary";s:2166:"h3a href=http://izandi.net/2009/04/free-wordpress-themes-dreams-2-columns/Dreams/a/h3\npa href=http://izandi.net/Free_WordPress_Themes/Dreams/img title=Dreams src=http://weblogtoolscollection.com/b2-img/2009/04/dreams.gif alt=Dreams width=200 height=129 //a/p\npTwo column, widget ready, gravatar ready theme/p\nh3a href=http://www.acosmin.com/acosmintech-v1-free-wordpress-theme/Acosmintech/a/h3\npa href=http://acosmintech.acosmin.com/img title=Acosmintech src=http://weblogtoolscollection.com/b2-img/2009/04/acosmintech.gif alt=Acosmintech width=200 height=110 //a/p\npTwo sidebar, widget, gravatar and tag ready theme with SIFR for headings and an included PSD file/p\nh3a href=http://dansette.com/2009/04/free-wordpress-theme-corp/Corp/a/h3\npimg title=Corp src=http://weblogtoolscollection.com/b2-img/2009/04/corp.png alt=Corp width=200 height=150 //p\npCorp is a free WordPress theme, with a double-column right sidebar and a business style - a riot of black and grays in other words#8230; except that link and hover colors are fully customizable from the admin. Compatible with WP 2.7 threaded comments etc./p\nh3a href=http://3oneseven.com/13/niukita-wp-theme/Niukita/a/h3\npa href=http://wp2.3oneseven.com/index.php?wptheme=Niukitaimg title=niukita src=http://weblogtoolscollection.com/b2-img/2009/04/niukita.png alt=niukita width=200 height=154 //a/p\npThe Niukita WP theme, corporate styles with the Niukita WordPress theme, loaded with a “presidential” blue/white colour scheme and an options panel for full control over the frontpage layout, featuring a two column fluid layout with built in options panel, frontpage news slider and automatic SEO titles./p\nh3a href=http://rzepak.pure.pl/themptationpress-free-premium-wordpress-theme/ThemptationPress/a/h3\npa href=http://themptationpress.pure.pl/img title=themptationPress src=http://weblogtoolscollection.com/b2-img/2009/04/themptationpress.jpg alt=themptationPress width=200 height=46 //a/p\npTwo column theme, with four widget areas, dropdown menu, six background variations and ad management system/p\npAre you a theme author? a href=http://weblogtoolscollection.com/submit-news/Submit your theme/a to us./p";}i:48;a:7:{s:5:"title";s:33:"Dougal Campbell: Where’s Waldo?";s:4:"guid";s:33:"http://dougal.gunters.org/?p=1490";s:4:"link";s:54:"http://dougal.gunters.org/blog/2009/04/25/wheres-waldo";s:11:"description";s:2660:"pOr, more to the point, where#8217;s Dougal?/p\npSorry about the long silence here. After our son got out of the hospital from a href=http://dougal.gunters.org/blog/2009/03/02/homehis pneumonia/a, he had four weeks of therapy before he returned to regular school. I had to drive across town to drop him off and pick him up, which ate up around 3 hours of each day when all was said and done. I#8217;ve also tried to devote some time to taking care of some tasks around the house before I start my new job./p\npimg class=alignright size-full wp-image-1497 title=MailChimp Head src=http://dougal.gunters.org/wordpress/wp-content/uploads/2009/04/the-head.jpg alt=MailChimp Head width=119 height=119 /New job, you say? Yup. I#8217;m going to be working at a href=http://mailchimp.com/MailChimp/a (go ahead, post all your #8216;code monkey#8217; puns, get it out of your system). MailChimp is a service for managing email newsletter campaigns, with nicely formatted acronym title=HyperText Markup Languagespan class=capsHTML/span/acronym mail templates, and readership analytics. The team there is already doing a lot of nifty stuff, like when a href=http://www.mailchimp.com/blog/want-700000-html-email-templates/they used Amazon Mechanical Turk/a to help vet a large set of programmatically generated themes and color schemes. I#8217;m looking forward to seeing what I#8217;ll get to work on, both in the main service, and in their #8220;a href=http://www.mailchimp.com/labs/MailChimp Labs/a#8221; projects./p\npimg class=alignright size-full wp-image-1500 title=Drupal Logo src=http://dougal.gunters.org/wordpress/wp-content/uploads/2009/04/drupal-logo.jpg alt=Drupal Logo width=108 height=124 /I#8217;ve also been dipping my toes into a href=http://drupal.org/Drupal/a a little bit lately. My wife, a href=http://digitaldivas.net/Susan/a, uses Drupal at her job, and I figured it might be nice to offer her some real ideas every once in a while, instead of just saying, #8220;if you were using a href=http://wordpress.org/WordPress/a, I could help you figure out how to do that.#8221; And no, they emcan#8217;t/em just switch to WordPress, unfortunately img src=http://dougal.gunters.org/wordpress/wp-includes/images/smilies/icon_smile.gif alt=:) class=wp-smiley / Drupal does have a steep learning curve (if you really want to do more interesting things with it), but it also has some nifty architectural bits. While much of it still feels alien to me, some of it has more in common with WordPress than I expected. When I feel like I#8217;ve learned enough, I#8217;ll try to write up a WordPress/Drupal comparison (mostly from the developer#8217;s perspective)./p";s:7:"pubdate";s:31:"Sat, 25 Apr 2009 19:58:44 +0000";s:2:"dc";a:1:{s:7:"creator";s:6:"Dougal";}s:7:"summary";s:2660:"pOr, more to the point, where#8217;s Dougal?/p\npSorry about the long silence here. After our son got out of the hospital from a href=http://dougal.gunters.org/blog/2009/03/02/homehis pneumonia/a, he had four weeks of therapy before he returned to regular school. I had to drive across town to drop him off and pick him up, which ate up around 3 hours of each day when all was said and done. I#8217;ve also tried to devote some time to taking care of some tasks around the house before I start my new job./p\npimg class=alignright size-full wp-image-1497 title=MailChimp Head src=http://dougal.gunters.org/wordpress/wp-content/uploads/2009/04/the-head.jpg alt=MailChimp Head width=119 height=119 /New job, you say? Yup. I#8217;m going to be working at a href=http://mailchimp.com/MailChimp/a (go ahead, post all your #8216;code monkey#8217; puns, get it out of your system). MailChimp is a service for managing email newsletter campaigns, with nicely formatted acronym title=HyperText Markup Languagespan class=capsHTML/span/acronym mail templates, and readership analytics. The team there is already doing a lot of nifty stuff, like when a href=http://www.mailchimp.com/blog/want-700000-html-email-templates/they used Amazon Mechanical Turk/a to help vet a large set of programmatically generated themes and color schemes. I#8217;m looking forward to seeing what I#8217;ll get to work on, both in the main service, and in their #8220;a href=http://www.mailchimp.com/labs/MailChimp Labs/a#8221; projects./p\npimg class=alignright size-full wp-image-1500 title=Drupal Logo src=http://dougal.gunters.org/wordpress/wp-content/uploads/2009/04/drupal-logo.jpg alt=Drupal Logo width=108 height=124 /I#8217;ve also been dipping my toes into a href=http://drupal.org/Drupal/a a little bit lately. My wife, a href=http://digitaldivas.net/Susan/a, uses Drupal at her job, and I figured it might be nice to offer her some real ideas every once in a while, instead of just saying, #8220;if you were using a href=http://wordpress.org/WordPress/a, I could help you figure out how to do that.#8221; And no, they emcan#8217;t/em just switch to WordPress, unfortunately img src=http://dougal.gunters.org/wordpress/wp-includes/images/smilies/icon_smile.gif alt=:) class=wp-smiley / Drupal does have a steep learning curve (if you really want to do more interesting things with it), but it also has some nifty architectural bits. While much of it still feels alien to me, some of it has more in common with WordPress than I expected. When I feel like I#8217;ve learned enough, I#8217;ll try to write up a WordPress/Drupal comparison (mostly from the developer#8217;s perspective)./p";}i:49;a:7:{s:5:"title";s:67:"Weblog Tools Collection: Blogging and WordPress links for 4/25/2009";s:4:"guid";s:40:"http://weblogtoolscollection.com/?p=5674";s:4:"link";s:94:"http://weblogtoolscollection.com/archives/2009/04/25/blogging-and-wordpress-links-for-4252009/";s:11:"description";s:1834:"pa href=http://www.studiopress.com/tips/how-to-use-the-wordpress-image-uploader-to-create-thumbnails.htmHow to use the WordPress image uploader to create thumbnails/a.: Brian explains how to automatically generate thumbnails (and resize images into various sizes) for your pictures using the WordPress image uploader./p\npa href=http://wpengineer.com/embed-wordpress-functions-outside-wordpress/How to embed WordPress functions outside of WordPress/a.: WP Engineer explains how to embed WordPress functions into code that is outside of WordPress. This can be very versatile and can help extend the usefulness of any WordPress install but would obviously require custom code./p\npa href=http://justintadlock.com/archives/2009/04/15/how-to-widgetize-your-page-menu-in-wordpressHow to widgetize your page menu in WordPress/a.: Justin explains a simple method to widgetize your menu of pages on your WordPress blog. Once you do that, the page menu can be treated as any other widget./p\npa href=http://blog.penelopetrunk.com/2009/04/21/8-reasons-why-you-wont-make-money-from-your-blog/Reality Check: You are not going to make money from your blog/a.: Penelope#8217;s interesting take on the views of the numerous MMO blogs out there and worth a read for everyone thinking of making a ton of money from blogging. I can attest that it is very hard to do and requires a lot more than just luck and perseverance for the rest of us, especially if you want to hold on to your principles and do the right thing./p\npa href=http://en.blog.wordpress.com/2009/04/23/comment-reply-via-email-open-to-all/WordPress.com: Comment reply via email/a. Now you can reply to comments on a WordPress.com blog just by replying to emails. This feature would be fantastic on hosted blogs but I can only presume the amount of setup and maintenance it would require./p";s:7:"pubdate";s:31:"Sat, 25 Apr 2009 17:01:37 +0000";s:2:"dc";a:1:{s:7:"creator";s:10:"Mark Ghosh";}s:7:"summary";s:1834:"pa href=http://www.studiopress.com/tips/how-to-use-the-wordpress-image-uploader-to-create-thumbnails.htmHow to use the WordPress image uploader to create thumbnails/a.: Brian explains how to automatically generate thumbnails (and resize images into various sizes) for your pictures using the WordPress image uploader./p\npa href=http://wpengineer.com/embed-wordpress-functions-outside-wordpress/How to embed WordPress functions outside of WordPress/a.: WP Engineer explains how to embed WordPress functions into code that is outside of WordPress. This can be very versatile and can help extend the usefulness of any WordPress install but would obviously require custom code./p\npa href=http://justintadlock.com/archives/2009/04/15/how-to-widgetize-your-page-menu-in-wordpressHow to widgetize your page menu in WordPress/a.: Justin explains a simple method to widgetize your menu of pages on your WordPress blog. Once you do that, the page menu can be treated as any other widget./p\npa href=http://blog.penelopetrunk.com/2009/04/21/8-reasons-why-you-wont-make-money-from-your-blog/Reality Check: You are not going to make money from your blog/a.: Penelope#8217;s interesting take on the views of the numerous MMO blogs out there and worth a read for everyone thinking of making a ton of money from blogging. I can attest that it is very hard to do and requires a lot more than just luck and perseverance for the rest of us, especially if you want to hold on to your principles and do the right thing./p\npa href=http://en.blog.wordpress.com/2009/04/23/comment-reply-via-email-open-to-all/WordPress.com: Comment reply via email/a. Now you can reply to comments on a WordPress.com blog just by replying to emails. This feature would be fantastic on hosted blogs but I can only presume the amount of setup and maintenance it would require./p";}}s:7:"channel";a:5:{s:5:"title";s:16:"WordPress Planet";s:4:"link";s:28:"http://planet.wordpress.org/";s:8:"language";s:2:"en";s:11:"description";s:47:"WordPress Planet - http://planet.wordpress.org/";s:7:"tagline";s:47:"WordPress Planet - http://planet.wordpress.org/";}s:9:"textinput";a:0:{}s:5:"image";a:0:{}s:9:"feed_type";s:3:"RSS";s:12:"feed_version";s:3:"2.0";s:5:"stack";a:0:{}s:9:"inchannel";b:0;s:6:"initem";b:0;s:9:"incontent";b:0;s:11:"intextinput";b:0;s:7:"inimage";b:0;s:13:"current_field";s:0:"";s:17:"current_namespace";b:0;s:19:"_CONTENT_CONSTRUCTS";a:6:{i:0;s:7:"content";i:1;s:7:"summary";i:2;s:4:"info";i:3;s:5:"title";i:4;s:7:"tagline";i:5;s:9:"copyright";}s:4:"etag";s:25:""2a2ac-4a029519-5042b6"\r\n";s:13:"last_modified";s:31:"Thu, 07 May 2009 08:00:25 GMT\r\n";}', 'no');
