(61, 1, '2009-01-20 00:39:30', '2009-01-20 05:39:30', '\r\n<p class="dropcap">This is my first time writing command for <strong><a href="http://ubiquity.mozilla.com/" target="_blank">Ubiquity</a></strong>, the wonderful Firefox plugin. The command is "juku", for a website <a href="http://www.jukuu.com" target="_blank">www.jukuu.com</a>. I use this script to retrive a word''s pronounce and example sentences, it supports English-Chinese and Chinese-English translations, the effect is like the image below:</p>\r\n<img src="http://sealence.x10hosting.com/wordpress/wp-content/uploads/2009/01/juku.JPG" alt="Ubiquity for jukuu.com" />\r\n\r\nYou can find the script on Github(another cool code share services base on Git):\r\n\r\n<a href="http://gist.github.com/49305" target="_blank">http://gist.github.com/49305</a>', 'Ubiquity Command: Jukuu', 0, '', 'publish', 'open', 'open', '', 'ubiquity-script-jukuu', '', '', '2009-01-22 21:28:35', '2009-01-23 02:28:35', '', 0, 'http://sealence.x10hosting.com/wordpress/?p=61', 0, 'post', '', 0),
(62, 1, '2009-01-20 20:28:22', '2009-01-21 01:28:22', '\r\n<h2 style="text-align: left">Ubiquity</h2>\r\n<hr style="margin: 20px; display: block" /><strong>juku</strong>: Retrive a word’s pronounce and example sentences from www.jukuu.com, supports English-Chinese and Chinese-English translations. <a href="http://sealence.x10hosting.com/wordpress/?p=61" target="_blank">Preview here.</a>\r\nCode: <a href="http://gist.github.com/49305" target="_blank">http://gist.github.com/49305</a>\r\n<strong>irecite</strong>: Retrieving 5 words from the every day recite word lists from www.iciba.com. None input for today''s word, input date string like "2009-1-19" to retrieve previous day. <a href="http://sealence.x10hosting.com/wordpress/?p=63" target="_blank">Preview here.</a>\r\nCode: <a href="http://gist.github.com/49422" target="_blank">http://gist.github.com/49422</a>\r\n<strong>cambridge</strong>: Search words in the <a href="http://dictionary.cambridge.org/" target="_blank">cambridge </a>dictionary. Click listed words can jump into each definitions.<a href="http://sealence.x10hosting.com/wordpress/?p=66" target="_blank">Preview here.</a>\r\nCode: <a href="http://gist.github.com/65093" target="_blank">http://gist.github.com/65093</a>', 'Projects', 0, '', 'publish', 'closed', 'open', '', 'projects', '', '', '2009-02-16 04:55:57', '2009-02-16 09:55:57', '', 0, 'http://sealence.x10hosting.com/wordpress/?page_id=62', 1, 'page', '', 0),
(63, 1, '2009-01-20 21:22:57', '2009-01-21 02:22:57', '\r\n<p class="dropcap">Another Ubiquity command "irecite", retrieving 5 words from the every day recite word lists from www.iciba.com. None input for today''s word, input date string like "2009-1-19" to retrieve previous day.</p>\r\n<img src="http://sealence.x10hosting.com/wordpress/wp-content/uploads/2009/01/irecite.JPG" alt="recite 5 english words everyday" />\r\n\r\n<a href="http://gist.github.com/49422" target="_blank">http://gist.github.com/49422 </a>\r\n\r\nEnjoy! :)', 'Ubiquity Command: Recite word every day', 0, '', 'publish', 'open', 'open', '', 'ubiquity-recite-word-every-day', '', '', '2009-01-20 21:32:55', '2009-01-21 02:32:55', '', 0, 'http://sealence.x10hosting.com/wordpress/?p=63', 0, 'post', '', 0),
