(66, 1, '2009-02-16 04:47:43', '2009-02-16 09:47:43', '<p class="dropcap">Search words in the <a href="http://dictionary.cambridge.org/" target="_blank">cambridge </a>dictionary. Click listed words can jump into each definitions.</p>\r\n\r\n<img src="http://sealence.x10hosting.com/wordpress/wp-content/uploads/2009/02/cambridge.JPG" alt="cambridge" />\r\n\r\n<a href="http://gist.github.com/65093" target="_blank">http://gist.github.com/65093</a>\r\n\r\nEnjoy! :)', 'Ubiquity Command: cambridge', 0, '', 'publish', 'open', 'open', '', 'ubiquity-command-cambridge', '', '', '2009-03-05 22:47:10', '2009-03-06 03:47:10', '', 0, 'http://sealence.x10hosting.com/wordpress/?p=66', 0, 'post', '', 0),
(67, 1, '2009-04-07 22:42:23', '2009-04-08 03:42:23', '\r\n<p class="dropcap">Debian 5.0 on QEMU, got following message:</p>\r\n<p>Apr  8 07:14:09 debian kernel: [   50.033169] Error: Driver ''pcspkr'' is already registered, aborting...</p>\r\nSolution:\r\n\r\n<a href="http://bugs.debian.org/cgi-bin/bugreport.cgi?bug=495674&amp;trim=no" target="_blank">http://bugs.debian.org/cgi-bin/bugreport.cgi?bug=495674&amp;trim=no</a>\r\n\r\nAdd a blacklist  in /etc/modprobe.d/blacklist\r\n<pre line="1" lang="bash">blacklist snd-pcsp</pre>', 'Debian: Driver ''pcspkr'' is already registered, aborting...', 0, '', 'publish', 'open', 'open', '', 'debian-driver-pcspkr-is-already-registered-aborting', '', '', '2009-04-07 22:48:04', '2009-04-08 03:48:04', '', 0, 'http://sealence.x10hosting.com/wordpress/?p=67', 0, 'post', '', 2),
(68, 1, '2009-05-07 02:59:50', '2009-05-07 07:59:50', '\r\n<p class="dropcap">Fastcgi is not in Debian main package, due to its licence not all free and so I use  fcgid instead.</p>\r\nlibapache2-mod-fcgid - an alternative module compat with mod_fastcgi\r\n\r\nFollowing is my http.conf:\r\n<pre line="1" lang="apache">\r\n<Directory "/usr/lib/cgi-bin/">\r\n        AllowOverride All\r\n        Options +ExecCGI -MultiViews +SymLinksIfOwnerMatch\r\n        Order allow,deny\r\n        Allow from all\r\n\r\n        # fcgid\r\n        AddHandler fcgid-script .cgi .pl .pm\r\n        <FilesMatch "^mt-(add-notify|atom|check|config|feed|testbg|upgrade|wizard|xmlrpc)\\.cgi$">\r\n            SetHandler cgi-script\r\n        </FilesMatch>\r\n</Directory>\r\n</pre>\r\nThere is no need to use FCGIWrapper, if that, won''t work.', 'How to: Configure fastcgid with perl', 0, '', 'publish', 'open', 'open', '', 'how-to-configure-fastcgid-with-perl', '', '', '2009-05-07 03:02:02', '2009-05-07 08:02:02', '', 0, 'http://sealence.x10hosting.com/wordpress/?p=68', 0, 'post', '', 0);
